Use simplified language in day to day communications, giving due consideration to any cultural sensitivities.</li><li>Select the right communication tool for the right task, and not necessarily the most efficient one best suited to your work habits.</li>','',''),(758,1,5,1,1,'','C','<li>Formulate employee resource groups, or networks of employees who share an affiliation (such as women, ethnic minorities, or young professionals).</li><li>Within the resource groups seek real assignments that are of tangible benefit to the business.</li>\n','',''),(759,1,6,1,1,'','C','<li>Model and promotes a culture of respect, fairness and trust where people feel appreciated and valued for their unique contribution.</li><li>Recognise individuals\' achievements, knowledge and capabilities.</li><li>Demonstrates openness to others\' ideas or to being influenced about another person (e.g., believing that others have something valuable to say or offer, no matter what position(s) they hold).</li><li>Facilitate open and honest dialogue and create a safe environment to learn, give and receive feedback.</li>','',''),(760,1,1,1,2,'','A','<li>Include opportunities for staff to interact in settings outside of work so that employees feel more comfortable.</li><li>Create Intranet-based multicultural calendars to avoid scheduling important meetings on major cultural holidays.</li>','','<li>Inclusive Leadership</li><li>Unconscious Bias</li><li>Managing Diversity &amp; Inclusion</li>'),(761,1,2,1,2,'','A','<li>Challenge unequal social norms where they become evident.</li><li>Strive to create gender friendly working patterns.</li>','',''),(762,1,3,1,2,'','A','<li>Include opportunities for staff to interact in settings outside of work so that employees feel more comfortable.</li><li>Be aware of, and provide time off for, culturally significant events and holy days.</li>','',''),(763,1,4,1,2,'','A','<li>Avoid using gender specific metaphors in business communications. Check all business communications are gender neutral.</li><li>Engage consulting experts who specialise in diversity training based on region, nationalities, or gender. Provide a documented policy for employees to review, discuss, and adhere to.</li>','',''),(764,1,5,1,2,'','A','<li>Ensure the team can have a dialogue to determine what they’re doing well and what they can do to improve.</li><li>Use attitude towards diversity to determine whether an employee is viewed as a good fit for the organisation.</li><li>Support mentorship and sponsorship opportunities within and across teams.</li>','',''),(765,1,6,1,2,'','A','<li>Share as much information as you can, as soon as you can. People want to know what is going on.</li><li>Lead from your values.</li><li>Share more about yourself, be real and be yourself.</li><li>Coach and develop others by providing timely and constructive feedback and showing sensitivity to diversity and diverse needs.</li>','',''),(766,1,1,1,2,'','B','<li>Be aware of, and provide time off for, culturally significant events and holy days.</li><li>Show individual interest, offering one-to-one support for people.</li><li>Allow all employees to make autonomous and unique contributions to progress both themselves and the organisation.</li>','','<li>Inclusive Leadership</li><li>Unconscious Bias</li><li>Managing Diversity &amp; Inclusion</li>'),(767,1,2,1,2,'','B','<li>Drive organisational attitudes and practices that yield equality, even if their recommendations are politically or culturally unpopular.</li><li>Exert considerable effort to identify own biases and learn ways to prevent them from influencing talent decisions.</li>','',''),(768,1,3,1,2,'','B','<li>Create Intranet-based multicultural calendars to avoid scheduling important meetings on major cultural holidays.</li>','',''),(769,1,4,1,2,'','B','<li>Establish ground rules for your team to collaborate. Clearly outline what is and is not acceptable.</li>','',''),(770,1,5,1,2,'','B','<li>Offer benefits that help employees balance their professional and personal commitments—such as flexible hours, on-site child care, and on-boarding support after a leave of absence.</li><li>Demonstrate openness and receptivity to any requested flexible arrangement (within reason).</li>','',''),(771,1,6,1,2,'','B','<li>Assigns decision making authority to front line employees or by those most responsible for the outcome.</li><li>Err on the side of sharing. If you aren’t sure if you should share, start by assuming you should and convince yourself not to.</li><li>Encourage questions, and answer them. \nShare your insight and help people see the bigger picture.</li><li>Think about timing and the wider picture when you are positioning a message, especially if that message is likely to be unpopular.</li>','',''),(772,1,1,1,2,'','C','<li>Show individual interest, offering one-to-one support for people.</li>','','<li>Inclusive Leadership</li><li>Unconscious Bias</li><li>Managing Diversity &amp; Inclusion</li>'),(773,1,2,1,2,'','C','<li>Ensure that all objectives are open and transparent and not driven by hidden agenda’s.</li>','',''),(774,1,3,1,2,'','C','<li>Be aware of, and provide time off for, culturally significant events and holy days.</li>','',''),(775,1,4,1,2,'','C','<li>Avoid using gender specific metaphors in business communications. Check all business communications are gender neutral.</li><li>Select the right communication tool for the right task, and not necessarily the most efficient one best suited to your work habits.</li><li>Establish ground rules for your team to collaborate. Clearly outline what is and is not acceptable.</li>','',''),(776,1,5,1,2,'','C','<li>Ensure the team can have a dialogue to determine what they’re doing well and what they can do to improve.</li><li>Track metrics during and after the hiring process.</li><li>Offer high-potential employees opportunities for external education and development.</li>','',''),(777,1,6,1,2,'','C','<li>Be consistent to create a ‘known quantity’ brand, which engenders trust.</li><li>Lead from your values.</li><li>Share more about yourself, be real and be yourself.</li><li>Delegate to others in order to provide them with opportunities for growth, all the while offering guidance, feedback and support to ensure success.</li><li>Coach and develop others by providing timely and constructive feedback and showing sensitivity to diversity and diverse needs.</li><li>Share own knowledge and best practice with others for the purpose of assisting in their on-going development.</li>','',''),(778,1,1,1,3,'','A','<li>Providing an appealing vision that inspires others.</li><li>Encouraging others to develop ideas and to be challenging.</li><li>Encouraging creative thinking throughout the business.</li>','','<li>Inclusive Leadership</li><li>Unconscious Bias</li><li>Managing Diversity &amp; Inclusion</li>'),(779,1,2,1,3,'','A','<li>Implement socially fair and gender sensitive policies.</li><li>Ensure diversity training mechanisms are in place for employees.</li><li>Ensure HR utilise diversity analytics in people decision making.</li>','',''),(780,1,3,1,3,'','A','<li>Apply business judge¬ment, evaluation and intuition that are free of bias.</li>','',''),(781,1,4,1,3,'','A','<li>Establish ground rules for your departments to collaborate. Clearly outline what is and is not acceptable.</li>','',''),(782,1,5,1,3,'','A','<li>Build a diversity-and-inclusion index that shows if people feel they are treated fairly and to help to ensure that people of diverse backgrounds can succeed.</li>','',''),(783,1,6,1,3,'','A','<li>Bring a positive energy to the organisation; communicate a collective purpose and create a clear line of sight to value proposition or change agenda.</li><li>Create an engaged work climate where staff understand the goals and objectives of the organisation or of the project or of the change.</li><li>Translate the organisation\'s vision, mission and values into terms that are relevant to the work being performed.</li><li>Provides leadership to others around how to execute strategies that transition the organisation from current to future state.</li><li>Be authentic; communicate a long-term vision of change that resounds with others, both within the group and beyond.</li><li>Genuinely listen to and addresses any resistance or concerns about the future of the organisation.</li>','',''),(784,1,1,1,3,'','B','<li>Providing opportunities for all employees to realise potential.</li><li>Consider the views of others in relation to wider operational and strategic outcomes.</li>','','<li>Inclusive Leadership</li><li>Unconscious Bias</li><li>Managing Diversity &amp; Inclusion</li>'),(785,1,2,1,3,'','B','<li>Implement policies, processes, and structures to prevent organisational biases from stifling diversity and inclusion.</li><li>Devise and communicate a clear business case for diversity.</li>','',''),(786,1,3,1,3,'','B','<li>Providing an appealing vision that inspires others.</li><li>Encouraging creative thinking throughout the business.</li>','',''),(787,1,4,1,3,'','B','<li>Engage consulting experts who specialize in diversity training based on region, nationalities, or gender. Provide a documented policy for employees to review, discuss, and adhere to.</li><li>Regularly evaluate your own communication \n   style, making calculated adjustments when needed with the sole purpose of achieving your goals.</li>','',''),(788,1,5,1,3,'','B','<li>Benchmark diversity objectives and have regular meetings around how to improve.</li><li>Put questions about diversity and inclusiveness into an employee engagement survey and compares the results annually.</li><li>Ensure that direct reports have things that they’re going to do personally to help promote diversity, not things that they can assign to their team.</li>','',''),(789,1,6,1,3,'','B','<li>Involve others in planning for and implementing change, and in so doing, gain their buy-in; help others deal with their resistance to change.</li><li>Communicate why change is needed, the benefits of change, what is at stake, and how the change will positively impact employees and the organisation.</li><li>Promote a climate of continuous transformation that will keep the organisation agile and \"best in class.\"</li><li>Ensure organisational processes and practices are aligned to values.</li>','',''),(790,1,1,1,3,'','C','<li>Demonstrate a respect for the importance of wellbeing, taking immediate action to address wellbeing issues.</li><li>Focus strategy on how employees’ skill sets contribute to long-term objectives.</li><li>Show a commitment to leading by serving others for the good of everyone rather than for self or top management interest.</li>','','<li>Inclusive Leadership</li><li>Unconscious Bias</li><li>Managing Diversity &amp; Inclusion</li>'),(791,1,2,1,3,'','C','<li>Use equality legislation more effectively to improve representation within the business.</li><li>Ensure diversity training mechanisms are in place for employees.</li>','',''),(792,1,3,1,3,'','C','<li>Implement socially fair and gender sensitive policies.</li><li>Encouraging creative thinking throughout the business.</li>','',''),(793,1,4,1,3,'','C','<li>Establish ground rules for your departments to collaborate. Clearly outline what is and is not acceptable.</li>','',''),(794,1,5,1,3,'','C','<li>Be intentional and populate the organisation with leaders who represent diversity.</li><li>Put questions about diversity and inclusiveness into an employee engagement survey and compares the results annually.</li><li>Ensure that direct reports have things that they’re going to do personally to help promote diversity, not things that they can assign to their team.</li><li>Benchmark diversity objectives and have regular meetings around how to improve.</li>','',''),(795,1,6,1,3,'','C','<li>Involve others in planning for and implementing change, and in so doing, gain their buy-in; help others deal with their resistance to change.</li><li>Promote a climate of continuous transformation that will keep the organisation agile and \"best in class.\"</li><li>Ensure organisational processes and practices are aligned to values.</li>','',''),(994,10,53,1,1,'','A','<li>Display confidence and seriousness to ensure that you will not be taken for granted.</li><li>Use words that can be easily understood, avoiding ambiguity.</li><li>Use visuals where possible to communicate a message to instil understanding.</li>','',''),(995,10,54,1,1,'','A','<li>When communicating diversity goals and objectives apply the 7 Cs, communication needs to be:\n     1. Clear.\n     2. Concise.\n     3. Concrete.\n     4. Correct.\n     5. Coherent.\n     6. Complete.\n     7. Courteous.</li><li>Consider the message you are attempting to deliver, against managing the message that the person/people receive.</li><li>Work on building your communication tool kit, develop and practice multiple approaches and phrases to use in different situations and with different people, and learn to read situations so that you can choose the best communication tool for the job.</li>','',''),(996,10,55,1,1,'','A','<li>Zero in on the source of any silence on a diversity issue, and examine what is driving it.</li><li>Make openness a routine; dedicate part of the agenda in your regular team meetings to air out problems.</li>','',''),(997,10,56,1,1,'','A','<li>Constructive feedback is information-specific, issue-focused, and based on observations.</li><li>Avoid “need to” phrases, which send implied messages that something that didn’t go well.</li><li>State observations, not interpretations. Observations are what you see occur; interpretations are your analysis or opinion of what you see occur.</li>','',''),(998,10,57,1,1,'','A','','',''),(999,10,58,1,1,'','A','','',''),(1000,10,53,1,1,'','B','<li>Always encourage two way communications.</li><li>Master the art of using body language when communicating with your team.</li><li>Act out your message and let people see you do what you want them to do.</li>','',''),(1001,10,54,1,1,'','B','','',''),(1002,10,55,1,1,'','B','<li>Model candour; run issues up the food chain to make employees more apt to come to you with an issue in relation to inclusion.</li>','',''),(1003,10,56,1,1,'','B','<li>Be sincere and avoid giving mixed messages.</li><li>Be direct when delivering your message.</li>','',''),(1004,10,57,1,1,'','B','<li>Recognise that, in many cases, the other person is not \"being difficult\" – real and valid differences can lie behind conflicting positions. Separate the problem from the person, in order to discuss issues without damaging relationships.</li><li>Get a better grasp of why people have adopted their position to understand their point of view.</li>','',''),(1005,10,58,1,1,'','B','<li>Have an obligation to understand not only the company\'s ethos but also the wider considerations of culturally different co-workers.</li><li>Work together, considering all viewpoints - and exercising courtesy and respect for each other.</li><li>Make no assumptions about culturally diverse individuals.</li><li>Learn to interpret body language.</li><li>Aim to create the right environment by bring co-workers together to discuss misconceptions and even hang-ups.</li><li>Separate facts from cultural assumptions and beliefs about those facts.</li>','',''),(1006,10,53,1,1,'','C','<li>Use appropriate tone of voice to communicate your message.</li><li>Check understanding.</li><li>Avoid a tense environment when you communicate key messages.</li><li>Ensure you are articulate.</li>','',''),(1007,10,54,1,1,'','C','','',''),(1008,10,55,1,1,'','C','','',''),(1009,10,56,1,1,'','C','<li>In positive feedback situations, express appreciation.</li><li>In negative feedback situations, express concern.</li><li>Give the feedback person-to-person, not through technology.</li>','',''),(1010,10,57,1,1,'','C','<li>Treat colleagues with respect. Do your best to be courteous, and to discuss matters constructively.</li><li>Listen to what the other person is saying before defending your own position.</li><li>Decide on the observable facts that might impact your decision, together.</li><li>Be open to the idea that a third position may exist, and that you might reach it jointly.</li>','',''),(1011,10,58,1,1,'','C','<li>Be prepared to learn about different cultures with an open mind; distinguish among facts, beliefs, values, and personal experience.</li><li>Create shared objectives.</li><li>Encourage your co-workers to share, learn and understand in order to get the job done.</li><li>Recognise other people\'s standards and values against the advantages they bring.</li>','',''),(1012,10,53,1,2,'','A','<li>Decide tactics in terms of how the communications process can be controlled.</li><li>Where appropriate, communicate widely so that individuals are given the opportunity to influence the process and local ownership is gained.</li><li>Make key communications as soon as possible following a significant event or decision.</li>','',''),(1013,10,54,1,2,'','A','<li>Put on your “real person” hat - And take off your “corporate person/executive” hat. Ensure messages are authentic.</li><li>Tell a story; ask employees to share stories as well, and use these as the foundation for dialogues that foster greater understanding of the behaviours that you want to encourage and enhance versus those that pose risks.</li>','',''),(1014,10,55,1,2,'','A','<li>Zero in on the source of any silence on a diversity issue, and examine what is driving it.</li><li>Give people context options to communicate; pay close attention to the gaps between the issues staff raise in a “safe, informal environment” versus the “issues that are discussed in team meetings.</li><li>Make sure everyone’s motivation to improve the organisation is sufficiently high.</li>','',''),(1015,10,56,1,2,'','A','<li>Μaintain employees’ dignity at all times.  Choose a quiet setting for the conversation and protect their privacy and confidentiality.</li><li>Be direct and specific in your language.  You need to be very clear what you are talking about.  Don’t leave it up to the individual to read between the lines.</li>','',''),(1016,10,57,1,2,'','A','<li>Take action when there is hard evidence/proof that an employee has a track record of wrongdoing that is negatively impacting the performance of others.</li><li>Know the risks and rewards of conflict resolution within the boundaries of each of your employees.</li>','',''),(1017,10,58,1,2,'','A','<li>Complete self-assessment to consider the influence of one\'s own biases and beliefs and the potential impact on service delivery.</li><li>Identify and acknowledge limitations in education, training, and knowledge and seek additional resources and education to bridge any identified gaps.</li>','',''),(1018,10,53,1,2,'','B','<li>If internal and external stakeholders are involved, internal staff should be communicated with prior to external stakeholders; this is to prevent staff hearing from other sources, including the media.</li><li>Ensure clear messages, related to the subject or problem.</li><li>In complex situations create a shared meaning and understanding.</li><li>Choose the most effective medium to get your message across.</li>','',''),(1019,10,54,1,2,'','B','<li>Aim to catch people somewhere that they would least expect it. Is it in the canteen? The stairwell? On their mobile phone?</li>','',''),(1020,10,55,1,2,'','B','<li>Make openness a routine; dedicate part of the agenda in your regular team meetings to air out problems.</li><li>Appoint someone whose job it is to bring up any diversity issues and concerns and then rotate that messenger role throughout the team over the course of time.</li>','',''),(1021,10,56,1,2,'','B','<li>Make sure you articulate how the sensitive issue relates to a specific performance concern.</li><li>Be clear as to whether you are just sharing concern for them on a personal level or if the issue has begun to negatively impact their performance.</li>','',''),(1022,10,57,1,2,'','B','<li>Help others know when they tend to cross the line through careful observation; identify behavioural tendencies that seem to trigger certain attitudes, provoke mindset shifts, or demonstrate a lack of self-awareness.</li><li>The new workplace represents a growing diversity in the types of people that are lead; get to know who they are in order to create an ecosystem that embraces difference.</li>','',''),(1023,10,58,1,2,'','B','<li>Seek funding for and engage in on-going professional development in aspects of cultural competence</li><li>Where possible integrate different traditions, customs, values, and beliefs in service delivery.</li><li>Uphold ethical responsibilities during service provision.</li>','',''),(1024,10,53,1,2,'','C','<li>Make time to communicate properly, do not do it in the corridor, or the car park.</li><li>Do the math and set your hoped-for ROI high whether it is financial performance or positive shifts in behaviour and culture.</li><li>Use 21st-century media and be unexpected; consider the social media, networking, blogs, and games to get the word out in ways that employees are used to engaging in.</li>','',''),(1025,10,54,1,2,'','C','<li>Do the math and set your hoped-for ROI high whether it is financial performance or positive shifts in behaviour and culture.</li><li>Use 21st-century media and be unexpected; consider the social media, networking, blogs, and games to get the word out in ways that employees are used to engaging in.</li>','',''),(1026,10,55,1,2,'','C','<li>Try to get to the source of colleagues’ concerns about speaking up in relation to diversity/inclusion what precisely are they afraid of?</li><li>Initiate one-on-one, informal conversations, which will help team members feel safer about broaching uncomfortable topics.</li><li>Create a culture where colleagues feel they have a stake in the future of the organisaiton and that speaking up about diversity issues is everyone’s job.</li>','',''),(1027,10,56,1,2,'','